{"type":"message","id":"31262c4d","parentId":"11b8b50d","timestamp":"2026-07-12T00:43:54.738Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_28d717d29e02496293753ea3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: linkedin-daily-brief\ndescription: Morning brief: researches today's news, drafts 2-3 ready-to-publish posts in user's brand voice. User taps Publish → auto-posts.\nuser-invocable: true\nmetadata: {\"openclaw\":{\"requires\":{\"env\":[\"LINKEDIN_CLIENT_ID\"]}}}\ntriggers:\n  - \"morning brief\"\n  - \"daily brief\"\n  - \"give me posts for today\"\n  - \"what should i post today\"\n  - \"ready posts\"\n  - \"draft posts for me\"\n  - \"what's happening in my industry\"\n  - \"brief me\"\n  - \"show me today's posts\"\n---\n\n# LinkedIn Daily Brief Skill\n\n> ⚠️ MANDATORY RULES:\n> 1. **Draft COMPLETE posts — not angles or ideas.** Every draft must be publish-ready in the user's voice.\n> 2. **Approve = immediate publish.** When the user taps ✅ Publish, call `li-post.sh` right away. No extra confirmation.\n> 3. **Per-user isolation.** All data keyed by `$TELEGRAM_USER_ID`.\n> 4. **Source everything.** Every draft must have a real, recent (≤48h) source URL.\n> 5. **DO NOT narrate steps.** Show results directly.\n> 6. **Max 3 drafts per day.** Quality over quantity.\n\n---\n\n## When this runs\n\n- **Daily cron** (8 AM user timezone) — fires before the coach check at 9 AM\n- **User manually asks** — \"give me posts for today\", \"morning brief\", etc.\n\n---\n\n## Flow A: Generate Morning Brief (cron or manual trigger)\n\n### Step 1 — Load user context (ONE bash block)\n\n```bash\nUID=\"${TELEGRAM_USER_ID}\"\nBASE=\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID\"\nTOKEN_STORE=/data/openclaw/linkedin-tokens.json\nTODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\nPENDING_DIR=\"$BASE/pending\"\n\n# OAuth check\nACCESS_TOKEN=*** -r --arg u \"$UID\" '.[$u].access_token // empty' \"$TOKEN_STORE\" 2>/dev/null)\nDISPLAY_NAME=$(jq -r --arg u \"$UID\" '.[$u].display_name // \"there\"' \"$TOKEN_STORE\" 2>/dev/null)\n\n# Check if brief already sent today\nBRIEF_FLAG=\"$PENDING_DIR/.brief-sent-$TODAY\"\n[ -f \"$BRIEF_FLAG\" ] && echo \"ALREADY_SENT=true\" || echo \"ALREADY_SENT=false\"\n\n# Load brand voice pillars and tone\nPILLARS=\"\"\nTONE=\"\"\nif [ -f \"$BASE/profile.md\" ]; then\n  PILLARS=$(grep -A 10 \"Content Pillars\\|pillars:\" \"$BASE/profile.md\" | head -12)\n  TONE=$(grep -A 5 \"Tone\\|Voice\\|Style\" \"$BASE/profile.md\" | head -6)\nfi\n\n# Load posting frequency context\nCADENCE=\"\"\nif [ -f \"$BASE/strategy.md\" ]; then\n  CADENCE=$(grep -i \"cadence\\|frequency\\|per week\\|posts/week\" \"$BASE/strategy.md\" | head -1)\nfi\n\n# Check posts already published today\nPOSTS_TODAY=$(find \"$BASE/posts/\" -name \"${TODAY}-*.md\" 2>/dev/null | wc -l | tr -d ' ')\n\nmkdir -p \"$PENDING_DIR\"\n\necho \"UID=$UID\"\necho \"NAME=$DISPLAY_NAME\"\necho \"TODAY=$TODAY\"\necho \"POSTS_TODAY=$POSTS_TODAY\"\necho \"PILLARS_BLOCK=$PILLARS\"\necho \"TONE_BLOCK=$TONE\"\n```\n\n**If no token / not connected:** Skip silently (cron) or route to onboarding (manual).\n**If `ALREADY_SENT=true` and manual trigger:** Proceed — user is explicitly asking for a refresh.\n**If `ALREADY_SENT=true` and cron trigger:** Skip silently.\n\n### Step 2 — Research today's news per pillar\n\nUse the user's content pillars to run targeted web searches. Find news published in the **last 48 hours**.\n\nFor each pillar (pick the 2-3 most relevant):\n```\nsearch: \"<pillar topic> news today 2026\" OR \"<pillar topic> latest\" site:techcrunch.com OR site:hbr.org OR site:venturebeat.com OR site:forbes.com\n```\n\nAlso run one broad signal search:\n```\nsearch: \"linkedin viral post today <user's industry>\"\n```\n\n**Quality bar:** Only use a story if:\n- Published within 48 hours (verify the date)\n- Directly relevant to at least one pillar\n- Has a clear opinion angle (not just \"X company did Y\")\n- Has a real URL you can cite\n\nDiscard anything older, vague, or already covered in the user's recent posts.\n\n**Target: 2-3 strong stories. Stop after finding 3 — don't over-research.**\n\n### Step 3 — Draft each post in the user's brand voice\n\nFor each story, write a complete LinkedIn post using ALL of these rules:\n\n**Post structure (Gary Vee framework from user's profile):**\n1. **Hook** (line 1): Bold claim, surprising stat, or provocative question. ≤12 words. No \"I\" opener.\n2. **Body** (lines 2-7): 3-5 punchy paragraphs, 1-2 sentences each. No fluff. Insight > information.\n3. **CTA** (last line): One direct question or call to action. Not \"thoughts?\" — be specific.\n4. **Hashtags** (after CTA): 3-5 from user's profile hashtag list.\n\n**Voice rules:**\n- Mirror the user's tone from `profile.md`\n- Write as if the user is speaking, not an AI summarising\n- Take a clear position — \"X matters because Y\" not \"X is interesting\"\n- Make it actionable: reader should learn something or want to do something\n\n**Length:** 150-250 words. Never shorter than 100 words or longer than 300.\n\n### Step 4 — Save drafts as pending files\n\nFor each draft (n = 1, 2, 3):\n\n```bash\nUID=\"${TELEGRAM_USER_ID}\"\nTODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\nPENDING_DIR=\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID/pending\"\nmkdir -p \"$PENDING_DIR\"\n\n# Save draft n (repeat for each)\ncat > \"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-<n>.md\" << 'DRAFT_EOF'\n---\ndate: <TODAY>\nn: <n>\npillar: <pillar name>\nsource: <source URL>\nsource_date: <source publication date>\nstatus: pending\n---\n\n<FULL POST TEXT — exactly what will be published>\nDRAFT_EOF\n\necho \"SAVED: $PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-<n>.md\"\n```\n\nMark brief as sent:\n```bash\ntouch \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID/pending/.brief-sent-$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\"\n```\n\n### Step 5 — Send drafts to user via Telegram\n\nSend a brief intro, then send each draft as a separate message with its own buttons.\n\n**Intro message:**\n```\nGood morning, <NAME>! ☀️\n\nHere are <N> posts ready to publish today — all based on fresh news from your industry. Tap ✅ to publish any immediately.\n```\n\n**For each draft, send this message:**\n```\n📝 Post <n>/<total> — <pillar name>\n\n<FULL POST TEXT>\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: <source title> (<source URL>)\n```\n\nWith buttons:\n```json\n{\n  \"action\": \"send\",\n  \"message\": \"📝 Post <n>/<total> — <pillar name>\\n\\n<FULL POST TEXT>\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: <source title> (<source URL>)\",\n  \"presentation\": {\n    \"blocks\": [\n      { \"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [\n        { \"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"action\": { \"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_<TODAY>-<n>\" }, \"style\": \"success\" },\n        { \"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\",  \"action\": { \"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_<TODAY>-<n>\" } },\n        { \"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\",        \"action\": { \"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_<TODAY>-<n>\" }, \"style\": \"secondary\" }\n      ]}\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n> Replace `<TODAY>` with the actual date (e.g. `2026-07-02`) and `<n>` with the draft number.\n> The callback value must be exact — it's used to load the right draft file.\n\n---\n\n## Flow B: Callback — Approve & Publish (`brief_approve_<date>-<n>`)\n\nWhen the incoming message matches `brief_approve_YYYY-MM-DD-<n>`:\n\n### Step 1 — Parse callback and load draft\n\n```bash\nCALLBACK=\"$1\"  # e.g. brief_approve_2026-07-02-1\n# Extract date and n from callback\nDATE_N=$(echo \"$CALLBACK\" | sed 's/brief_approve_//')\n# DATE_N is now e.g. \"2026-07-02-1\"\n# Split: last segment after final dash is n, rest is date\nN=\"${DATE_N##*-}\"\nDATE=\"${DATE_N%-*}\"\n\nUID=\"${TELEGRAM_USER_ID}\"\nDRAFT_FILE=\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID/pending/${DATE}-draft-${N}.md\"\n\nif [ ! -f \"$DRAFT_FILE\" ]; then\n  echo \"DRAFT_NOT_FOUND\"\n  exit 1\nfi\n\n# Extract post text (everything after the frontmatter ---)\nPOST_TEXT=$(awk '/^---/{count++; next} count==2{print}' \"$DRAFT_FILE\")\necho \"POST_TEXT_START\"\necho \"$POST_TEXT\"\necho \"POST_TEXT_END\"\n```\n\n**If `DRAFT_NOT_FOUND`:** Reply \"I can't find that draft — it may have already been published or expired. Use /linkedin-publish to post manually.\"\n\n### Step 2 — Publish immediately\n\n```bash\n{baseDir of linkedin-publish}/li-post.sh \"$TELEGRAM_USER_ID\" \"<POST_TEXT_EXTRACTED>\"\n```\n\nUse the `li-post.sh` helper from `linkedin-publish` skill. Path: `{skills dir}/linkedin-publish/li-post.sh`.\n\nOn success (`OK: <post_url>`):\n1. Move draft to published:\n```bash\nDATE_N=$(echo \"$CALLBACK\" | sed 's/brief_approve_//')\nN=\"${DATE_N##*-}\"\nDATE=\"${DATE_N%-*}\"\nSLUG=\"brief-$(date +%Y-%m-%d)-${N}\"\nUID=\"${TELEGRAM_USER_ID}\"\nmkdir -p \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID/posts\"\nmv \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID/pending/${DATE}-draft-${N}.md\" \\\n   \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID/posts/${SLUG}.md\"\n# Update status in file\nsed -i 's/^status: pending/status: published/' \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID/posts/${SLUG}.md\"\n```\n2. Reply with confirmation:\n```\n✅ Published!\n\n<POST_URL>\n\nGreat work showing up today, <NAME>. That's how brands are built.\n```\n\nOn failure: Show the error and offer to retry manually via `/linkedin-publish`.\n\n### Step 3 — Check remaining drafts\n\n```bash\nUID=\"${TELEGRAM_USER_ID}\"\nDATE=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\nREMAINING=$(ls \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID/pending/${DATE}-draft-\"*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l | tr -d ' ')\necho \"REMAINING=$REMAINING\"\n```\n\nIf `REMAINING > 0`: \"You have <N> more drafts from this morning. Check your earlier messages to publish them.\"\n\n---\n\n## Flow C: Callback — Edit Draft (`brief_edit_<date>-<n>`)\n\nWhen the incoming message matches `brief_edit_YYYY-MM-DD-<n>`:\n\n### Step 1 — Load draft\n\n```bash\nCALLBACK=\"$1\"\nDATE_N=$(echo \"$CALLBACK\" | sed 's/brief_edit_//')\nN=\"${DATE_N##*-}\"\nDATE=\"${DATE_N%-*}\"\nUID=\"${TELEGRAM_USER_ID}\"\nDRAFT_FILE=\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID/pending/${DATE}-draft-${N}.md\"\nPOST_TEXT=$(awk '/^---/{count++; next} count==2{print}' \"$DRAFT_FILE\")\necho \"$POST_TEXT\"\n```\n\n### Step 2 — Show draft and ask for edits\n\nSend the draft text with:\n```\nHere's draft <n>:\n\n<POST TEXT>\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nWhat should I change? Tell me (e.g. \"make it shorter\", \"add a stat\", \"change the tone to more casual\", \"rewrite the hook\") and I'll update it.\n```\n\nHand off to `linkedin-brand-voice` for the rewrite, then re-present with ✅ Publish / ✏️ Edit again / ⏭️ Skip buttons using the **same callback values** so approval still works.\n\nAfter rewriting, **overwrite the draft file** with the updated text so ✅ Publish picks up the new version.\n\n---\n\n## Flow D: Callback — Skip Draft (`brief_skip_<date>-<n>`)\n\nWhen the incoming message matches `brief_skip_YYYY-MM-DD-<n>`:\n\n```bash\nCALLBACK=\"$1\"\nDATE_N=$(echo \"$CALLBACK\" | sed 's/brief_skip_//')\nN=\"${DATE_N##*-}\"\nDATE=\"${DATE_N%-*}\"\nUID=\"${TELEGRAM_USER_ID}\"\nDRAFT_FILE=\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID/pending/${DATE}-draft-${N}.md\"\n[ -f \"$DRAFT_FILE\" ] && sed -i 's/^status: pending/status: skipped/' \"$DRAFT_FILE\"\n```\n\nReply:\n```\nGot it, skipped. 👍\n```\n\nNo further action. Don't offer alternatives unless the user asks.\n\n---\n\n## Flow E: All-Users Cron Run\n\nWhen cron fires without a specific `TELEGRAM_USER_ID`:\n\n```bash\nTOKEN_STORE=/data/openclaw/linkedin-tokens.json\n[ -f \"$TOKEN_STORE\" ] || exit 0\njq -r 'to_entries[] | select(.value.access_token != null and .value.access_token != \"\") | .key' \"$TOKEN_STORE\"\n```\n\nFor each user ID returned, run **Flow A** above with that user's `TELEGRAM_USER_ID`.\nSkip users with no profile.md (not yet set up).\n\n---\n\n## Brief quality rules (always apply)\n\n- **No generic takes.** \"AI is changing everything\" is noise. \"Here's the specific thing AI changed this week that affects [persona]\" is signal.\n- **Be opinionated.** A post without a point of view is forgettable.\n- **Real sources only.** Never cite a URL you haven't verified. Never fabricate publication dates.\n- **One idea per post.** Don't cram 3 insights into one post. Each draft = one clear idea.\n- **Short paragraphs.** LinkedIn renders single-line-break paragraphs. Write accordingly.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783817034733}}
{"type":"message","id":"8f4618d3","parentId":"31262c4d","timestamp":"2026-07-12T00:44:07.878Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ff81e11401ce4f7daa5a6cf3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"UID=\"264468965\"\nBASE=\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID\"\nTOKEN_STORE=/data/openclaw/linkedin-tokens.json\nTODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\nPENDING_DIR=\"$BASE/pending\"\n\n# OAuth check\nACCESS_TOKEN=*** -r --arg u \"$UID\" '.[$u].access_token // empty' \"$TOKEN_STORE\" 2>/dev/null)\nDISPLAY_NAME=$(jq -r --arg u \"$UID\" '.[$u].display_name // \"there\"' \"$TOKEN_STORE\" 2>/dev/null)\n\n# Check if brief already sent today\nBRIEF_FLAG=\"$PENDING_DIR/.brief-sent-$TODAY\"\n[ -f \"$BRIEF_FLAG\" ] && echo \"ALREADY_SENT=true\" || echo \"ALREADY_SENT=false\"\n\n# Load brand voice pillars and tone\nPILLARS=\"\"\nTONE=\"\"\nif [ -f \"$BASE/profile.md\" ]; then\n  PILLARS=$(grep -A 10 \"Content Pillars\\|pillars:\" \"$BASE/profile.md\" | head -12)\n  TONE=$(grep -A 5 \"Tone\\|Voice\\|Style\" \"$BASE/profile.md\" | head -6)\nfi\n\n# Load posting frequency context\nCADENCE=\"\"\nif [ -f \"$BASE/strategy.md\" ]; then\n  CADENCE=$(grep -i \"cadence\\|frequency\\|per week\\|posts/week\" \"$BASE/strategy.md\" | head -1)\nfi\n\n# Check posts already published today\nPOSTS_TODAY=$(find \"$BASE/posts/\" -name \"${TODAY}-*.md\" 2>/dev/null | wc -l | tr -d ' ')\n\nmkdir -p \"$PENDING_DIR\"\n\necho \"UID=$UID\"\necho \"NAME=$DISPLAY_NAME\"\necho \"TODAY=$TODAY\"\necho \"POSTS_TODAY=$POSTS_TODAY\"\necho \"PILLARS_BLOCK=$PILLARS\"\necho \"TONE_BLOCK=$TONE\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"UID=\\\"264468965\\\"\\nBASE=\\\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID\\\"\\nTOKEN_STORE=/data/openclaw/linkedin-tokens.json\\nTODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\\nPENDING_DIR=\\\"$BASE/pending\\\"\\n\\n# OAuth check\\nACCESS_TOKEN=$(jq -r --arg u \\\"$UID\\\" '.[$u].access_token // empty' \\\"$TOKEN_STORE\\\" 2>/dev/null)\\nDISPLAY_NAME=$(jq -r --arg u \\\"$UID\\\" '.[$u].display_name // \\\"there\\\"' \\\"$TOKEN_STORE\\\" 2>/dev/null)\\n\\n# Check if brief already sent today\\nBRIEF_FLAG=\\\"$PENDING_DIR/.brief-sent-$TODAY\\\"\\n[ -f \\\"$BRIEF_FLAG\\\" ] && echo \\\"ALREADY_SENT=true\\\" || echo \\\"ALREADY_SENT=false\\\"\\n\\n# Load brand voice pillars and tone\\nPILLARS=\\\"\\\"\\nTONE=\\\"\\\"\\nif [ -f \\\"$BASE/profile.md\\\" ]; then\\n  PILLARS=$(grep -A 10 \\\"Content Pillars\\\\|pillars:\\\" \\\"$BASE/profile.md\\\" | head -12)\\n  TONE=$(grep -A 5 \\\"Tone\\\\|Voice\\\\|Style\\\" \\\"$BASE/profile.md\\\" | head -6)\\nfi\\n\\n# Load posting frequency context\\nCADENCE=\\\"\\\"\\nif [ -f \\\"$BASE/strategy.md\\\" ]; then\\n  CADENCE=$(grep -i \\\"cadence\\\\|frequency\\\\|per week\\\\|posts/week\\\" \\\"$BASE/strategy.md\\\" | head -1)\\nfi\\n\\n# Check posts already published today\\nPOSTS_TODAY=$(find \\\"$BASE/posts/\\\" -name \\\"${TODAY}-*.md\\\" 2>/dev/null | wc -l | tr -d ' ')\\n\\nmkdir -p \\\"$PENDING_DIR\\\"\\n\\necho \\\"UID=$UID\\\"\\necho \\\"NAME=$DISPLAY_NAME\\\"\\necho \\\"TODAY=$TODAY\\\"\\necho \\\"POSTS_TODAY=$POSTS_TODAY\\\"\\necho \\\"PILLARS_BLOCK=$PILLARS\\\"\\necho \\\"TONE_BLOCK=$TONE\\\"\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4c61566ddde144a1a391e743","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/profile.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/profile.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783817034756,"responseId":"TONSasWBEZPl7bQPnPvr6QQ"}}
{"type":"message","id":"73e07505","parentId":"8f4618d3","timestamp":"2026-07-12T00:44:08.083Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ff81e11401ce4f7daa5a6cf3","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ALREADY_SENT=false\nUID=264468965\nNAME=Andrii Bidochko\nTODAY=2026-07-12\nPOSTS_TODAY=0\nPILLARS_BLOCK=## Content Pillars\n\n1. Business & entrepreneurship insights\n2. Technology & AI innovations\n3. Personal development & mindset\n\n## Company / Product Context\n\n- **Company:** UBOS (ubos.tech)\n- **What it does:** AI Agent Orchestration Platform - build, host, and manage AI Agents in minutes using open-source tools (Langchain, CrewAI, Autogen, Vertex AI), 100+ LLM models, one-click cloud/on-premise deployment\n- **Key differentiators:** No vendor lock-in (open-source, multi-cloud), unlimited agents as microservices, works with any LLM including self-hosted (Llama, Deepseek)\nTONE_BLOCK=# LinkedIn Brand Voice - Andrii Bidochko\n\n**Owner:** 264468965\n**Last updated:** 2026-07-06\n\n## Identity & Goals"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":66,"aggregated":"ALREADY_SENT=false\nUID=264468965\nNAME=Andrii Bidochko\nTODAY=2026-07-12\nPOSTS_TODAY=0\nPILLARS_BLOCK=## Content Pillars\n\n1. Business & entrepreneurship insights\n2. Technology & AI innovations\n3. Personal development & mindset\n\n## Company / Product Context\n\n- **Company:** UBOS (ubos.tech)\n- **What it does:** AI Agent Orchestration Platform - build, host, and manage AI Agents in minutes using open-source tools (Langchain, CrewAI, Autogen, Vertex AI), 100+ LLM models, one-click cloud/on-premise deployment\n- **Key differentiators:** No vendor lock-in (open-source, multi-cloud), unlimited agents as microservices, works with any LLM including self-hosted (Llama, Deepseek)\nTONE_BLOCK=# LinkedIn Brand Voice - Andrii Bidochko\n\n**Owner:** 264468965\n**Last updated:** 2026-07-06\n\n## Identity & Goals","cwd":"/data/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1783817048078}}
{"type":"message","id":"b300bb65","parentId":"73e07505","timestamp":"2026-07-12T00:44:08.090Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_4c61566ddde144a1a391e743","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# LinkedIn Brand Voice - Andrii Bidochko\n\n**Owner:** 264468965\n**Last updated:** 2026-07-06\n\n## Identity & Goals\n\n- **Target audience:** Business professionals, entrepreneurs, tech-savvy individuals seeking growth and insights\n- **Primary goal:** Maximum organic engagement (impressions, comments, shares) through thought leadership and value-driven content\n\n## Buyer Personas\n\n*(Who specifically should feel spoken to by every post)*\n\n- **Persona 1:** Enterprise Innovation Officer / CTO at 200+ person company (Financial Services, Healthcare, Retail) - Pain: Needs rapid AI solution development without vendor lock-in or heavy internal R&D\n- **Persona 2:** CTO / Software Architect at 75+ person IT consultancy or agency - Pain: Needs to deliver AI-powered client projects faster with reusable components\n- **Persona 3:** Founder / CEO / Head of Operations at 10-200 person SMB - Pain: Wants automation and AI competitiveness but lacks the engineering resources or budget\n\n## Content Pillars\n\n1. Business & entrepreneurship insights\n2. Technology & AI innovations\n3. Personal development & mindset\n\n## Company / Product Context\n\n- **Company:** UBOS (ubos.tech)\n- **What it does:** AI Agent Orchestration Platform - build, host, and manage AI Agents in minutes using open-source tools (Langchain, CrewAI, Autogen, Vertex AI), 100+ LLM models, one-click cloud/on-premise deployment\n- **Key differentiators:** No vendor lock-in (open-source, multi-cloud), unlimited agents as microservices, works with any LLM including self-hosted (Llama, Deepseek)\n- **Mission:** \"Help people build better software\"\n- **Key messages to reinforce:**\n  1. AI can be affordable and accessible - even for small businesses\n  2. Implementing AI doesn't require a big team or deep tech expertise\n  3. Every company will become AI-first - the question is when, not if\n  4. **Benchmark-first AI Agent development** — The best way to build self-evolving AI agents is to start with a verifiable benchmark and reward function (like TDD for software). Define the outcome BEFORE the agent, then let it optimize toward it.\n\n## Voice & Tone\n\n- **Style:** Gary Vaynerchuk (Gary Vee) - Direct, energetic, bold, motivational, conversational. Short punchy lines, strong opinions, urgency. Powerful language with strong verbs, imperative statements, and intensifiers (\"absolutely,\" \"definitely,\" \"100%\"). Keep it real and direct with colloquial language. Create urgency with \"right now,\" \"immediately.\" Use repetition for emphasis. Casual but pointed tone.\n- **Avoid:** Neutral reporting, corporate/formal tone, vague humble-brags, excessive emojis (max 0-3 per post), generic hashtags (#success, #motivation), salesy CTAs\n\n## Hashtag Strategy\n\n- Always use: 3-6 hashtags placed at the END of the post only\n- Topic-specific: Industry, role, or topic-specific hashtags preferred\n- Never use hashtags inside sentences\n\n## Post Production Rules\n\n*(Apply to EVERY post - non-negotiable)*\n\n### Length & Structure\n- Target: 900-1,300 characters (hard min 800, max 1,400)\n- Max 14 lines total; 1-2 short sentences per line\n- Structure: 1-3 hook lines -> 6-10 body lines -> 1-2 CTA lines\n\n### Hook rules\n- Pattern interrupt - ONE of: contrarian statement, direct challenge, consequence reveal\n- Unicode bold sans for hook line ONLY - no Markdown, no *, no _\n\n### Body rules\n- ONE comment trigger: direct question, A vs B, or unfinished thought\n- Contrast: old belief vs reality, OR short-term comfort vs long-term cost\n- ONE save-worthy insight: a rule, checklist, or named pattern\n- \"you\" and \"your\" throughout; ALL CAPS on 1-2 key words max\n- Speak directly to a buyer persona's pain\n- Gary Vee style ALWAYS takes precedence over any example post tone\n\n### CTA rules\n- Question, never a command; no selling language\n\n### Hashtag rules\n- 3-6 at END only; never inside sentences; prefer industry/role/topic-specific\n- Avoid: #success, #motivation\n\n### Formatting rules\n- NO Markdown; Unicode emphasis on hook/key phrase only, never full paragraphs\n- Emojis: 0-3 max per post\n\n### News framing\n- Reframe using ONE angle: \"What this means for you\" / \"Why this is underestimated\" / \"The mistake most people will make\" / \"The second-order effect nobody mentions\"\n- Never neutral reporting - always add perspective, judgment, or implication\n- If engagement feels weak after drafting - rewrite hook and CTA once before finalizing\n\n## Post Style Guide\n\n- Length: 900-1,300 characters\n- CTA style: question-based\n- Format: calibrate from feedback\n\n## History\n\n- **2026-06-25** | Profile created via detailed configuration import\n- **2026-06-25** | Enriched with Buyer Personas, Company/Product Context (UBOS), consolidated Post Production Rules\n- **2026-07-06** | Added Key Message #4: Benchmark-first AI Agent development (TDD parallel for self-evolving agents)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783817048087}}
