{"type":"message","id":"a2d27847","parentId":"c79abc73","timestamp":"2026-07-12T01:44:12.112Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ca216624cd79477daedaa09b","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -1 /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/*.md 2>/dev/null | grep -E \"2026-07-(0[5-9]|1[0-2])\" | wc -l"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"ls -1 /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/*.md 2>/dev/null | grep -E \\\"2026-07-(0[5-9]|1[0-2])\\\" | wc -l\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_e4419c3673324bc9bc4a1f47","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/content-calendar.md","limit":50},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/content-calendar.md\", \"limit\": 50}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783820644219,"responseId":"ZfFSatu6MpbZ7bQP7srswAY"}}
{"type":"message","id":"412bb477","parentId":"a2d27847","timestamp":"2026-07-12T01:44:12.200Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ca216624cd79477daedaa09b","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"14"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":15,"aggregated":"14","cwd":"/data/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1783820652195}}
{"type":"message","id":"5c7a68a6","parentId":"412bb477","timestamp":"2026-07-12T01:44:12.207Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_e4419c3673324bc9bc4a1f47","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Content Calendar — Andrii Bidochko\n\n**Owner:** 264468965\n**Last updated:** 2026-07-06\n\n---\n\n## Scheduled Posts — Benchmark-First AI Agent Series\n\n### Post 1: The anatomy of a good benchmark (July 7, 9:00 AM UTC)\n\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Key Message:** #4 — Benchmark-first AI Agent development\n**Status:** 📅 Scheduled for auto-publish\n\n**Draft:**\n\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗱𝗶𝗳𝗳𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗻𝗰𝗲 𝗯𝗲𝘁𝘄𝗲𝗲𝗻 𝗮 𝗵𝗼𝗽𝗲𝗳𝘂𝗹 𝗔𝗜 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗷𝗲𝗰𝘁 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗮 𝘀𝗲𝗹𝗳-𝗲𝘃𝗼𝗹𝘃𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗼𝗻𝗲?\n\nOne has a benchmark. The other has vibes.\n\nA good benchmark answers three questions:\n\n1. **What's the task?** (specific, not vague)\n2. **What does \"done\" look like?** (verifiable outcome)\n3. **How do you measure it?** (quantifiable metric)\n\nMost teams skip this. They build the agent first, then scramble to figure out if it's working.\n\nFlip it. Write the benchmark BEFORE a single line of code. Make it pass. Then make the agent chase it.\n\nThe benchmark IS your reward function. Every iteration moves the needle. Every failure teaches the system.\n\nThis is TDD for AI. Test first. Agent second.\n\nWhat's one AI project you're building without a clear benchmark?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #TDD #MachineLearning #SoftwareEngineering\n\n**Characters:** ~950\n\n---\n\n### Post 2: Why most AI agents drift (July 7, 3:00 PM UTC)\n\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Key Message:** #4 — Benchmark-first AI Agent development\n**Status:** ✅ Published — https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7480274563235254272/\n\n**Draft:**\n\n[91 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783820652204}}
