{"type":"message","id":"ce5b1e51","parentId":"c033e1dc","timestamp":"2026-07-12T07:14:26.903Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_eea502b97a61437f85c65948","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"/data/workspace/skills/linkedin-publish/li-post.sh \"264468965\" image \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/boring-agents-1783699220.png\" \"𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗖𝗥𝗠 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗯𝗲𝗰𝗮𝗺𝗲 𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗿𝘆𝗼𝗻𝗲'𝘀 𝘁𝗼𝗼𝗹.\n\nSlackbot now connects directly to Salesforce — CRM records, Tableau dashboards, DocuSign approvals — all from a chat message. No switching tabs. No learning a new interface. Just ask.\n\nFor 25 years, Salesforce was for salespeople. Maybe 20% of your company. Now anyone in a Slack channel can pull a customer profile, see pipeline trends, and trigger next steps.\n\nThe CMO calls it \\\"multiplayer AI.\\\" I call it obvious.\n\nMost AI tools are single-player. You prompt. The AI answers. The insight dies in your private chat. Your team never sees it.\n\nSlack's bet: the agent belongs in the channel. Everyone sees the question. Everyone sees the answer. Everyone can correct, redirect, or build on it.\n\nThe real unlock isn't the tech. It's that your CRM investment just became useful to 100% of your workforce instead of 20%.\n\nHow much Salesforce budget have you spent that only your sales team can access?\n\n#AI #EnterpriseAI #Salesforce #Slack #MultiplayerAI\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"/data/workspace/skills/linkedin-publish/li-post.sh \\\"264468965\\\" image \\\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/boring-agents-1783699220.png\\\" \\\"𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗖𝗥𝗠 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗯𝗲𝗰𝗮𝗺𝗲 𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗿𝘆𝗼𝗻𝗲'𝘀 𝘁𝗼𝗼𝗹.\\n\\nSlackbot now connects directly to Salesforce — CRM records, Tableau dashboards, DocuSign approvals — all from a chat message. No switching tabs. No learning a new interface. Just ask.\\n\\nFor 25 years, Salesforce was for salespeople. Maybe 20% of your company. Now anyone in a Slack channel can pull a customer profile, see pipeline trends, and trigger next s