{"type":"message","id":"d0a93a0a","parentId":"4f54d06f","timestamp":"2026-07-12T07:14:48.759Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_485d609f1b32416ca1bf5f1e","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"add","job":{"deleteAfterRun":true,"name":"LinkedIn Post 2 - Sovereign access risk","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Publish this LinkedIn post NOW for user 264468965. Use this image: /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/boring-agents-1783699220.png\n\nPost text:\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗜 𝗺𝗼𝗱𝗲𝗹 𝗱𝗶𝘀𝗮𝗽𝗽𝗲𝗮𝗿𝗲𝗱 𝗼𝘃𝗲𝗿𝗻𝗶𝗴𝗵𝘁. 𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗦𝗟𝗔 𝗱𝗶𝗱𝗻'𝘁 𝗰𝗼𝘃𝗲𝗿 𝗶𝘁.\n\nThree weeks ago, the US government disabled Anthropic's Fable 5 for every foreign national. No warning. No exception. Just gone.\n\nEnterprise contracts didn't help. Force majeure clauses. Compliance catch-alls. Nothing about a government kill switch.\n\nThat event created a new risk category: sovereign access risk. When a government can flip off your AI model overnight, pricing and benchmarks become secondary.\n\nZ.ai just shipped the answer: GLM-5.2, MIT-licensed, trained entirely on Huawei chips, 82% cheaper than Claude Opus 4.8. Download it. Host it yourself. No export controls. No foreign kill switch.\n\nThe catch: if you use their cloud, Chinese law applies. The only way out is pure self-hosting.\n\nThis isn't about picking a model. It's about asking: Will this tool still work tomorrow? And who decides?\n\nYour vendor's SLA doesn't cover geopolitics.\n\n#AI #EnterpriseAI #Sovereignty #OpenSource #Geopolitics","toolsAllow":["exec","read","write"]},"schedule":{"at":"2026-07-12T09:13:00Z","kind":"at"},"sessionTarget":"isolated"}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"add\", \"job\": {\"deleteAfterRun\": true, \"name\": \"LinkedIn Post 2 - Sovereign access risk\", \"payload\": {\"kind\": \"agentTurn\", \"message\": \"Publish this LinkedIn post NOW for user 264468965. Use this image: /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/boring-agents-1783699220.png\\n\\nPost text:\\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗜 𝗺𝗼𝗱𝗲𝗹 𝗱𝗶𝘀𝗮𝗽𝗽𝗲𝗮𝗿𝗲𝗱 𝗼𝘃𝗲𝗿𝗻𝗶𝗴𝗵𝘁. 𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗦𝗟𝗔 𝗱𝗶𝗱𝗻'𝘁 𝗰𝗼𝘃𝗲𝗿 𝗶𝘁.\\n\\nThree weeks ago, the US government disabled Anthropic's Fable 5 for every foreign national. No warning. No exception. Just gone.\\n\\nEnterprise contracts didn't help. Force majeure clauses. Compliance catch-alls. Nothing about a government kill switch.\\n\\nThat event created a new risk category: sovereign access risk. When a government can flip off your AI model overnight, pricing and benchmarks become secondary.\\n\\nZ.ai just shipped the answer: GLM-5.2, MIT-licensed, trained entirely on Huawei chips, 82% cheaper than Claude Opus 4.8. Download it. Host it yourself. No export controls. No foreign kill switch.\\n\\nThe catch: if you use their cloud, Chinese law applies. The only way out is pure self-hosting.\\n\\nThis isn't about picking a model. It's about asking: Will this tool still work tomorrow? And who decides?\\n\\nYour vendor's SLA doesn't cover geopolitics.\\n\\n#AI #EnterpriseAI #Sovereignty #OpenSource #Geopolitics\", \"toolsAllow\": [\"exec\", \"read\", \"write\"]}, \"schedule\": {\"at\": \"2026-07-12T09:13:00Z\", \"kind\": \"at\"}, \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ab32d8591b874c5cb7529a85","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"add","job":{"deleteAfterRun":true,"name":"LinkedIn Post 3 - AI usage not coding","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Publish this LinkedIn post NOW for user 264468965. Use this image: /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/boring-agents-1783699220.png\n\nPost text:\n𝟵𝟭% 𝗼𝗳 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘂𝘀𝗮𝗴𝗲 𝗶𝘀𝗻'𝘁 𝗰𝗼𝗱𝗶𝗻𝗴.\n\nNew data from 1.2 million Claude Cowork sessions:\n→ 33.4% business process and operations\n→ 16.4% content creation\n→ 8.7% software development\n\nThe dominant use case isn't writing code. It's \"the work around the work\" — status reports, slide decks, onboarding checklists, variance memos.\n\nThe stuff that every role has to do but no one's job title includes.\n\nEveryone's been optimizing for developers. Anthropic just mapped the real market: every knowledge worker with a laptop and a pile of spreadsheets.\n\nMobile and web launch this week. Schedule a task at 6 AM. Claude works through the email threads and transcripts while you sleep. Review it over coffee.\n\nThe shift: AI isn't here to do your job. It's here to do everything around your job so you can focus on the part that matters.\n\nWhat's the \"work around the work\" eating your week?\n\n#AI #Productivity #EnterpriseAI #KnowledgeWork #Automation","toolsAllow":["exec","read","write"]},"schedule":{"at":"2026-07-12T11:13:00Z","kind":"at"},"sessionTarget":"isolated"}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"add\", \"job\": {\"deleteAfterRun\": true, \"name\": \"LinkedIn Post 3 - AI usage not coding\", \"payload\": {\"kind\": \"agentTurn\", \"message\": \"Publish this LinkedIn post NOW for user 264468965. Use this image: /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/boring-agents-1783699220.png\\n\\nPost text:\\n𝟵𝟭% 𝗼𝗳 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘂𝘀𝗮𝗴𝗲 𝗶𝘀𝗻'𝘁 𝗰𝗼𝗱𝗶𝗻𝗴.\\n\\nNew data from 1.2 million Claude Cowork sessions:\\n→ 33.4% business process and operations\\n→ 16.4% content creation\\n→ 8.7% software development\\n\\nThe dominant use case isn't writing code. It's \\\"the work around the work\\\" — status reports, slide decks, onboarding checklists, variance memos.\\n\\nThe stuff that every role has to do but no one's job title includes.\\n\\nEveryone's been optimizing for developers. Anthropic just mapped the real market: every knowledge worker with a laptop and a pile of spreadsheets.\\n\\nMobile and web launch this week. Schedule a task at 6 AM. Claude works through the email threads and transcripts while you sleep. Review it over coffee.\\n\\nThe shift: AI isn't here to do your job. It's here to do everything around your job so you can focus on the part that matters.\\n\\nWhat's the \\\"work around the work\\\" eating your week?\\n\\n#AI #Productivity #EnterpriseAI #KnowledgeWork #Automation\", \"toolsAllow\": [\"exec\", \"read\", \"write\"]}, \"schedule\": {\"at\": \"2026-07-12T11:13:00Z\", \"kind\": \"at\"}, \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6270c358d72f4e32a3e8b9df","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Your CRM just became everyone's tool\n\n**Published:** 2026-07-12T07:13:00Z\n**LinkedIn URL:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7481969216141664257/\n**Post URN:** urn:li:share:7481969216141664257\n**Format:** image\n**Characters:** 1083\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Image:** /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/boring-agents-1783699220.png\n\n## Post Body\n\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗖𝗥𝗠 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗯𝗲𝗰𝗮𝗺𝗲 𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗿𝘆𝗼𝗻𝗲'𝘀 𝘁𝗼𝗼𝗹.\n\nSlackbot now connects directly to Salesforce — CRM records, Tableau dashboards, DocuSign approvals — all from a chat message. No switching tabs. No learning a new interface. Just ask.\n\nFor 25 years, Salesforce was for salespeople. Maybe 20% of your company. Now anyone in a Slack channel can pull a customer profile, see pipeline trends, and trigger next steps.\n\nThe CMO calls it \"multiplayer AI.\" I call it obvious.\n\nMost AI tools are single-player. You prompt. The AI answers. The insight dies in your private chat. Your team never sees it.\n\nSlack's bet: the agent belongs in the channel. Everyone sees the question. Everyone sees the answer. Everyone can correct, redirect, or build on it.\n\nThe real unlock isn't the tech. It's that your CRM investment just became useful to 100% of your workforce instead of 20%.\n\nHow much Salesforce budget have you spent that only your sales team can access?\n\n#AI #EnterpriseAI #Salesforce #Slack #MultiplayerAI\n\n## Performance\n\n*(populated later by linkedin-analytics)*\n\n- **Impressions:** —\n- **Reactions:** —\n- **Comments:** —\n- **Shares:** —\n- **Last checked:** —\n","path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-12-your-crm-just-became-everyones.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"content\": \"# Your CRM just became everyone's tool\\n\\n**Published:** 2026-07-12T07:13:00Z\\n**LinkedIn URL:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7481969216141664257/\\n**Post URN:** urn:li:share:7481969216141664257\\n**Format:** image\\n**Characters:** 1083\\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\\n**Image:** /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/boring-agents-1783699220.png\\n\\n## Post Body\\n\\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗖𝗥𝗠 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗯𝗲𝗰𝗮𝗺𝗲 𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗿𝘆𝗼𝗻𝗲'𝘀 𝘁𝗼𝗼𝗹.\\n\\nSlackbot now connects directly to Salesforce — CRM records, Tableau dashboards, DocuSign approvals — all from a chat message. No switching tabs. No learning a new interface. Just ask.\\n\\nFor 25 years, Salesforce was for salespeople. Maybe 20% of your company. Now anyone in a Slack channel can pull a customer profile, see pipeline trends, and trigger next steps.\\n\\nThe CMO calls it \\\"multiplayer AI.\\\" I call it obvious.\\n\\nMost AI tools are single-player. You prompt. The AI answers. The insight dies in your private chat. Your team never sees it.\\n\\nSlack's bet: the agent belongs in the channel. Everyone sees the question. Everyone sees the answer. Everyone can correct, redirect, or build on it.\\n\\nThe real unlock isn't the tech. It's that your CRM investment just became useful to 100% of your workforce instead of 20%.\\n\\nHow much Salesforce budget have you spent that only your sales team can access?\\n\\n#AI #EnterpriseAI #Salesforce #Slack #MultiplayerAI\\n\\n## Performance\\n\\n*(populated later by linkedin-analytics)*\\n\\n- **Impressions:** —\\n- **Reactions:** —\\n- **Comments:** —\\n- **Shares:** —\\n- **Last checked:** —\\n\", \"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-12-your-crm-just-became-everyones.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783840470087,"responseId":"1z5TasH4AsnDwOYPsqWLgQc"}}
