{"type":"message","id":"987fa0dd","parentId":"9c48e409","timestamp":"2026-07-13T00:16:33.070Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_88adc456c96d449998a9ac32","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"Good morning, Andrii! ☀️\n\nHere are 3 posts ready to publish today — all based on fresh news from your industry. Tap ✅ to publish any immediately."},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"Good morning, Andrii! ☀️\\n\\nHere are 3 posts ready to publish today — all based on fresh news from your industry. Tap ✅ to publish any immediately.\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7196f2b549ad45faa6f83d25","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 1/3 — Technology & AI innovations\n\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗻𝗲𝘅𝘁 𝗔𝗚𝗜 𝗯𝗿𝗲𝗮𝗸𝘁𝗵𝗿𝗼𝘂𝗴𝗵 𝗺𝗶𝗴𝗵𝘁 𝗰𝗼𝗺𝗲 𝗳𝗿𝗼𝗺 𝘃𝗶𝗱𝗲𝗼 𝗴𝗮𝗺𝗲𝘀, 𝗻𝗼𝘁 𝘁𝗲𝘅𝘁.\n\nGeneral Intuition just raised $320M at a $2.3B valuation — Bezos, Eric Schmidt, Coatue, MIT, DeepMind researchers all in. Their bet: LLMs hit a wall because they don't understand how things move through space and time.\n\nGaming data does.\n\nThink about it. A model trained on Minecraft learns physics, causality, spatial reasoning — all the stuff text can't teach. The company spun out of Medal TV, a gaming platform. They're not guessing. They have the data pipeline.\n\nThe race to AGI has been stuck on \"more text, bigger models.\" This is the first credible pivot to a different training paradigm.\n\nEveryone's optimizing for scale. The winners will optimize for the right data.\n\nHow much of your AI strategy is just \"use bigger models\" vs \"use better training data\"?\n\n#AI #AGI #MachineLearning #Gaming #FutureOfWork\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: TechCrunch - Why this CEO thinks video games make better training data than the internet (https://techcrunch.com/video/why-this-ceo-thinks-video-games-make-better-training-data-than-the-internet/)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"buttons":[{"action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_approve_2026-07-13-1"},"label":"✅ Publish now","style":"success"},{"action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_edit_2026-07-13-1"},"label":"✏️ Edit first"},{"action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_skip_2026-07-13-1"},"label":"⏭️ Skip","style":"secondary"}],"type":"buttons"}]}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"📝 Post 1/3 — Technology & AI innovations\\n\\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗻𝗲𝘅𝘁 𝗔𝗚𝗜 𝗯𝗿𝗲𝗮𝗸𝘁𝗵𝗿𝗼𝘂𝗴𝗵 𝗺𝗶𝗴𝗵𝘁 𝗰𝗼𝗺𝗲 𝗳𝗿𝗼𝗺 𝘃𝗶𝗱𝗲𝗼 𝗴𝗮𝗺𝗲𝘀, 𝗻𝗼𝘁 𝘁𝗲𝘅𝘁.\\n\\nGeneral Intuition just raised $320M at a $2.3B valuation — Bezos, Eric Schmidt, Coatue, MIT, DeepMind researchers all in. Their bet: LLMs hit a wall because they don't understand how things move through space and time.\\n\\nGaming data does.\\n\\nThink about it. A model trained on Minecraft learns physics, causality, spatial reasoning — all the stuff text can't teach. The company spun out of Medal TV, a gaming platform. They're not guessing. They have the data pipeline.\\n\\nThe race to AGI has been stuck on \\\"more text, bigger models.\\\" This is the first credible pivot to a different training paradigm.\\n\\nEveryone's optimizing for scale. The winners will optimize for the right data.\\n\\nHow much of your AI strategy is just \\\"use bigger models\\\" vs \\\"use better training data\\\"?\\n\\n#AI #AGI #MachineLearning #Gaming #FutureOfWork\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: TechCrunch - Why this CEO thinks video games make better training data than the internet (https://techcrunch.com/video/why-this-ceo-thinks-video-games-make-better-training-data-than-the-internet/)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"buttons\": [{\"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-13-1\"}, \"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-13-1\"}, \"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\"}, {\"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-13-1\"}, \"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"style\": \"secondary\"}], \"type\": \"buttons\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c40002494e7d428e89ef3290","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 2/3 — Technology & AI innovations\n\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗜 𝗶𝗻𝗳𝗿𝗮𝘀𝘁𝗿𝘂𝗰𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲 𝗽𝗹𝗮𝗻 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗵𝗶𝘁 𝗮 𝗵𝗮𝗿𝗱𝘄𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝘄𝗮𝗹𝗹.\n\nDRAM and NAND flash are sold out through 2027. Samsung and SK hynix are dropping $518B on new fabs — but capacity won't come online until late 2027 or 2028.\n\nMicron is meeting only 50-67% of customer demand right now. Sandisk/Kioxia just announced their 10th gen NAND with 332 layers — but that takes time to scale.\n\nThe bottleneck isn't compute. It's memory. And it's going to get worse before it gets better.\n\nThree moves for anyone building AI infrastructure:\n1. Lock in memory supply contracts now — spot prices will keep climbing\n2. Optimize inference efficiency — you won't be able to brute-force your way through\n3. Consider model distillation — smaller models need less memory\n\nThe cloud providers are fighting for the same chips you are. The ones with memory secured win.\n\nWhen's the last time you checked your memory allocation strategy?\n\n#AI #Infrastructure #Hardware #DataCenter #CloudComputing\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: Forbes - Memory Capacity Production Slowly Expanding To Meet AI Industry Demand (https://www.forbes.com/sites/tomcoughlin/2026/07/12/memory-capacity-production-slowly-expanding-to-meet-ai-industry-demand/)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"buttons":[{"action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_approve_2026-07-13-2"},"label":"✅ Publish now","style":"success"},{"action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_edit_2026-07-13-2"},"label":"✏️ Edit first"},{"action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_skip_2026-07-13-2"},"label":"⏭️ Skip","style":"secondary"}],"type":"buttons"}]}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"📝 Post 2/3 — Technology & AI innovations\\n\\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗜 𝗶𝗻𝗳𝗿𝗮𝘀𝘁𝗿𝘂𝗰𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲 𝗽𝗹𝗮𝗻 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗵𝗶𝘁 𝗮 𝗵𝗮𝗿𝗱𝘄𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝘄𝗮𝗹𝗹.\\n\\nDRAM and NAND flash are sold out through 2027. Samsung and SK hynix are dropping $518B on new fabs — but capacity won't come online until late 2027 or 2028.\\n\\nMicron is meeting only 50-67% of customer demand right now. Sandisk/Kioxia just announced their 10th gen NAND with 332 layers — but that takes time to scale.\\n\\nThe bottleneck isn't compute. It's memory. And it's going to get worse before it gets better.\\n\\nThree moves for anyone building AI infrastructure:\\n1. Lock in memory supply contracts now — spot prices will keep climbing\\n2. Optimize inference efficiency — you won't be able to brute-force your way through\\n3. Consider model distillation — smaller models need less memory\\n\\nThe cloud providers are fighting for the same chips you are. The ones with memory secured win.\\n\\nWhen's the last time you checked your memory allocation strategy?\\n\\n#AI #Infrastructure #Hardware #DataCenter #CloudComputing\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: Forbes - Memory Capacity Production Slowly Expanding To Meet AI Industry Demand (https://www.forbes.com/sites/tomcoughlin/2026/07/12/memory-capacity-production-slowly-expanding-to-meet-ai-industry-demand/)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"buttons\": [{\"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-13-2\"}, \"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-13-2\"}, \"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\"}, {\"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-13-2\"}, \"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"style\": \"secondary\"}], \"type\": \"buttons\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3ed0f1f39d8f461cb361fc3e","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 3/3 — Business & entrepreneurship insights\n\n𝗦𝗮𝗺𝘀𝘂𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗦𝗞 𝗵𝘆𝗻𝗶𝘅 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗯𝗲𝘁 $𝟱𝟭𝟴 𝗯𝗶𝗹𝗹𝗶𝗼𝗻 𝗼𝗻 𝗔𝗜'𝘀 𝗳𝘂𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲.\n\nThat's not a typo. $518 billion. Four new memory fabs. One packaging hub. Announced with Korea's President.\n\nThe context: These two companies control two-thirds of the world's DRAM. They're sold out through 2027. Prices are skyrocketing. AI data centers are starving for memory.\n\nSK hynix's chair said it took 9 years to build their current capability. These new fabs? Same timeline if they started today.\n\nThe signal: The companies building AI's physical infrastructure are making decade-long bets. They're not optimizing for quarterly earnings. They're positioning for who owns the next wave.\n\nMost AI discourse is about models and applications. The real game is being played at the hardware layer — and it's a 10-year chess match.\n\nAre you building for this quarter or this decade?\n\n#AI #Business #Strategy #Infrastructure #LongTermThinking\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: Forbes - Memory Capacity Production Slowly Expanding To Meet AI Industry Demand (https://www.forbes.com/sites/tomcoughlin/2026/07/12/memory-capacity-production-slowly-expanding-to-meet-ai-industry-demand/)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"buttons":[{"action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_approve_2026-07-13-3"},"label":"✅ Publish now","style":"success"},{"action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_edit_2026-07-13-3"},"label":"✏️ Edit first"},{"action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_skip_2026-07-13-3"},"label":"⏭️ Skip","style":"secondary"}],"type":"buttons"}]}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"📝 Post 3/3 — Business & entrepreneurship insights\\n\\n𝗦𝗮𝗺𝘀𝘂𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗦𝗞 𝗵𝘆𝗻𝗶𝘅 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗯𝗲𝘁 $𝟱𝟭𝟴 𝗯𝗶𝗹𝗹𝗶𝗼𝗻 𝗼𝗻 𝗔𝗜'𝘀 𝗳𝘂𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲.\\n\\nThat's not a typo. $518 billion. Four new memory fabs. One packaging hub. Announced with Korea's President.\\n\\nThe context: These two companies control two-thirds of the world's DRAM. They're sold out through 2027. Prices are skyrocketing. AI data centers are starving for memory.\\n\\nSK hynix's chair said it took 9 years to build their current capability. These new fabs? Same timeline if they started today.\\n\\nThe signal: The companies building AI's physical infrastructure are making decade-long bets. They're not optimizing for quarterly earnings. They're positioning for who owns the next wave.\\n\\nMost AI discourse is about models and applications. The real game is being played at the hardware layer — and it's a 10-year chess match.\\n\\nAre you building for this quarter or this decade?\\n\\n#AI #Business #Strategy #Infrastructure #LongTermThinking\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: Forbes - Memory Capacity Production Slowly Expanding To Meet AI Industry Demand (https://www.forbes.com/sites/tomcoughlin/2026/07/12/memory-capacity-production-slowly-expanding-to-meet-ai-industry-demand/)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"buttons\": [{\"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-13-3\"}, \"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-13-3\"}, \"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\"}, {\"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-13-3\"}, \"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"style\": \"secondary\"}], \"type\": \"buttons\"}]}}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783901722411,"responseId":"HC5Uav7lFqvx3PQPgd-yiAo"}}
{"type":"message","id":"97bb17e9-baf1-455d-8917-32cb9e8d8ac9","parentId":"987fa0dd","timestamp":"2026-07-13T00:16:33.576Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good morning, Andrii! ☀️\n\nHere are 3 posts ready to publish today — all based on fresh news from your industry. Tap ✅ to publish any immediately."}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1783901793532,"idempotencyKey":"ed2356d0-e20d-4a09-9cbd-5bd5809544d7:message-tool:EUP2R2w8Zsj37Edbun7yxcSD:call_88adc456c96d449998a9ac32"}}
