{"type":"message","id":"8e78056a","parentId":"c0494b46","timestamp":"2026-07-13T05:14:19.346Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f7032aa2b93840f0a647237e","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Samsung and SK hynix just bet $518 billion on AI's future\n\n**Published:** 2026-07-13T05:13:00Z\n**LinkedIn URL:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7482301331215388672/\n**Post URN:** urn:li:share:7482301331215388672\n**Format:** image\n**Characters:** 1040\n**Pillar:** Business & entrepreneurship insights\n**Image:** /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/boring-agents-1783699220.png\n\n## Post Body\n\n𝗦𝗮𝗺𝘀𝘂𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗦𝗞 𝗵𝘆𝗻𝗶𝘅 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗯𝗲𝘁 $𝟱𝟭𝟴 𝗯𝗶𝗹𝗹𝗶𝗼𝗻 𝗼𝗻 𝗔𝗜'𝘀 𝗳𝘂𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲.\n\nThat's not a typo. $518 billion. Four new memory fabs. One packaging hub. Announced with Korea's President.\n\nThe context: These two companies control two-thirds of the world's DRAM. They're sold out through 2027. Prices are skyrocketing. AI data centers are starving for memory.\n\nSK hynix's chair said it took 9 years to build their current capability. These new fabs? Same timeline if they started today.\n\nThe signal: The companies building AI's physical infrastructure are making decade-long bets. They're not optimizing for quarterly earnings. They're positioning for who owns the next wave.\n\nMost AI discourse is about models and applications. The real game is being played at the hardware layer — and it's a 10-year chess match.\n\nAre you building for this quarter or this decade?\n\n#AI #Business #Strategy #Infrastructure #LongTermThinking\n\n## Performance\n\n*(populated later by linkedin-analytics)*\n\n- **Impressions:** —\n- **Reactions:** —\n- **Comments:** —\n- **Shares:** —\n- **Last checked:** —\n","path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-13-samsung-and-***.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"content\": \"# Samsung and SK hynix just bet $518 billion on AI's future\\n\\n**Published:** 2026-07-13T05:13:00Z\\n**LinkedIn URL:** https